  "physical_interpretation": "When the Leeuwin Current delivers warm water early (Jan-Feb already near peak habitat), blue marlin arrive and establish in the Perth Canyon sooner, creating a longer effective fishing season. Years where habitat conditions ramp up late (large Jan-to-Mar jump) have shorter windows and fewer catches. This is consistent with marlin being migratory apex predators that track warm water masses - earlier warmth means earlier arrival.",
